# Exploratory Data Analysis on Amazon Prime TV Shows and Movies

## Project Overview

This project performs **Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA)** on the Amazon Prime Video dataset to uncover insights about movies and TV shows available on the platform. The analysis focuses on identifying trends in genres, ratings, production countries, and content growth over time.

The dataset contains information about **9000+ titles and 120k+ credits** including actors and directors. Using data analysis and visualization techniques, this project reveals patterns that can help businesses understand content strategies and audience engagement.

---

## Business Objective

The main objective of this project is to **analyze Amazon Prime Video data to identify trends and insights** that influence content production, popularity, and platform growth.

Key questions addressed in this project:

* What type of content dominates the platform (Movies vs Shows)?
* Which genres are most common on Amazon Prime?
* How has content production changed over the years?
* Which countries contribute the most titles?
* How do IMDb and TMDB ratings compare?
* What is the relationship between runtime, popularity, and ratings?

---

## Dataset Description

The dataset consists of **two CSV files**:

### 1. titles.csv

Contains information about all titles available on Amazon Prime.

Columns include:

* id – Unique title ID
* title – Name of the title
* type – Movie or TV Show
* description – Short description
* release_year – Year of release
* age_certification – Content rating
* runtime – Duration of movie/show
* genres – Genre categories
* production_countries – Country of production
* seasons – Number of seasons (for shows)
* imdb_id – IMDb identifier
* imdb_score – IMDb rating
* imdb_votes – Number of IMDb votes
* tmdb_popularity – Popularity score from TMDB
* tmdb_score – TMDB rating

### 2. credits.csv

Contains information about actors and directors.

Columns include:

* person_id – Person identifier
* id – Title identifier
* name – Actor/Director name
* character – Character name
* role – Role (Actor or Director)

